 Available experimental data were interpreted  using              8125 1451
 nuclear reaction model code EMPIRE-3 by M. Herman                8125 1451
 et al [EMP]. This code integrates into a single                  8125 1451
 system a number of important modules and features:               8125 1451
                                                                  8125 1451
 - Spherical and deformed Optical Model including                 8125 1451
   coupled-channels (ECIS06 by J. Raynal)                         8125 1451
 - Hauser-Feshbach statistical model including                    8125 1451
   HRTW width fluctuation correction                              8125 1451
 - Quantum-mechanical MSD TUL model (codes ORION &                8125 1451
   TRISTAN by H. Lenske), and MSC NVWY model                      8125 1451
 - Exciton model with angular momentum coupling                   8125 1451
   (code DEGAS by E. Betak and P. Oblozinsky) that                8125 1451
   represents a good approximation to the DSD model               8125 1451
 - Exciton model with Iwamoto-Harada cluster                      8125 1451
   emission and Kalbach systematic angular distr.                 8125 1451
   (code PCROSS by R.Capote et al)                                8125 1451
 - Complete gamma-ray cascade after emission of                   8125 1451
   each particle, including realistic treatment of                8125 1451
   discrete transitions                                           8125 1451
 - Access to OM segment of the RIPL library [RIPL]                8125 1451
 - Built-in input parameter files, such as masses,                8125 1451
   level density, discrete levels, fission barriers               8125 1451
   and gamma strength functions based on the RIPL                 8125 1451
   library [RIPL]                                                 8125 1451
 - Automatic retrieval of experimental data from the              8125 1451
   EXFOR/CSISRS library                                           8125 1451
 - ENDF-6 formatting (code EMPEND by A. Trkov)                    8125 1451
   coupled to graphical presentation capabilities                 8125 1451
   (code ZVView by V. Zerkin) through the chain of                8125 1451
   PrePro codes by R. Cullen                                      8125 1451
 - Checking codes (CHECKR, FIZCON, PSYCHE)                        8125 1451
 - Support for NJOY                                               8125 1451
